}
\section{Changes in version 1.8.1 (2014-03-14)}{
  \itemize{
    \item{Examplar designs converted to Windows EOL for better compatibility.}
    \item{Examplar designs now only enforces non-default parameters.}
    \item{'rescue' argument added to align.fsa(), "rescue.conf" updated accordingly.}
    \item{Designs with empty PEAKS section no longer raise errors in designFile().}
    \item{align.fsa() no longer stops if too many peaks are detected, warns instead.}
    \item{align.fsa() default for 'fullLadder' is now complete.}
    \item{designFile() no longer warns if an argument is set to default, sends a message instead.}
    \item{MLPA.interface() now displays warning counts at the end of processing, if any.}
    \item{read.fsa() and MLPA.process() now handle a selection of metadata from the FSA file.}
    \item{model() no longer enforces a default for 'groupNames'.}
  }
}
\section{Changes in version 1.8.0 (2014-02-28)}{
  \itemize{
    \item{model() and classify() added, designFile() modified accordingly.}
    \item{Commas replaced by tabulations in designFile() for vectors.}
    \item{Normalization now occurs in getMax().}
    \item{getPeaks() and Ruminy... functions deleted, as deprecated.}
    \item{align.fsa() can now mask indexes with off-scale value in any channel.}
    \item{Package dataset replaced.}
    \item{Rescue design added.}
    \item{MLPA.process() now reminds design file in log (with MD5 checksum if available).}
    \item{plot.fsa() better handles 'chanColors' when 'channels' is not default.}
    \item{"rescue.conf" design file added.}
  }
}
\section{Changes in version 1.7.1 (2014-01-31)}{
  \itemize{
    \item{MLPA.interface() manual resizing better controled.}
    \item{Trailing spaces and tabulations no longer invalidate design files.}
    \item{'chanCol' argument to plot.fsa() renamed into 'chanColors'.}
    \item{'units', 'channels', 'chanCol', 'xlab', 'xlim', 'ylim' and 'xaxp' default values turned to NA.}
    \item{"[plot.fsa]" section now handled by designFile().}
    \item{'xlim' and 'ylim' removed from MLPA.interface() and MLPA.process() (moved into design).}
    \item{"[align.fsa]" and "[plot.fsa]" sections are now optional in design files.}
    \item{'modelMode' removed from MLPA.interface() and MLPA.process() until implementation.}
    \item{ 4 more examples of .fsa files shiped in the 'extdata' directory.}
  }
}
\section{Changes in version 1.7.0 (2014-01-29)}{
  \itemize{
    \item{Applied Biosystems' binary converter replaced by seqinr package's read.abif(), enabling compatibility with most operating systems.}
    \item{Dependency to XML package dropped, dependency to tcltk made optional.}
    \item{Windows file selection dialogues replaced by Tcl-tk ones.}
    \item{Examples added to most of the help pages.}
    \item{offScale attribute in 'fsa' objects simplified as vectors (channel data seems spurious).}
    \item{outThreshold argument in align.fsa() can now be defined as a proportion (new default value).}
    \item{MLPA.interface() no longer proposes a default design path (second occurence removed).}
    \item{modelizeNoise() deleted, as deprecated.}
  }
}
\section{Changes in version 1.6.0 (2014-01-24)}{
  \itemize{
    \item{Design files now include more settings, old files must be rewritten accordingly.}
    \item{An example of design file is now provided in the package directory.}
    \item{align.fsa() rewritten for more precision and robustness (may invalidate old intervals).}
    \item{MLPA.interface() gave birth to MLPA.process() for harmonization with CLI processing.}
    \item{Peak mode option removed from MLPA.interface().}
    \item{MLPA.interface() is now resizable.}
    \item{plot.fsa() no longer plots offscale values from unselected channels.}
    \item{ruminyLPS() is now exported in the NAMESPACE.}
    \item{read.fsa() now expects NA for default converter, no more NULL.}
    \item{MLPA.interface() no longer proposes a default design path.}
  }
}
